content.p:
some documents are generated by HMPPS on a rolling basis; for instance, the offenders OASys

OASys is the abbreviated term for the Offender Assessment System used in England and Wales by HMPPS from 2002 to measure the risks and needs of criminal offenders under their supervision.
		 report is based on a dynamic risk assessment which is subject to constant review. It follows that a direction for disclosure on a rolling basis may well be of more assistance to the expert instructed and to the court than merely an assessment prepared at a particular point in time;
